<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346248>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Polystemma stevensii. A. Flowering branch. B. Frontal view of a flower. C. Detail of gynostegial corona showing appendages and five lobes fused basally to form a flat discontinuous ring. D. Pollinarium. E. Branch with a follicle. Illustration by Ericka B. Cortez." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346248/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346250>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Polystemma stevensii. A. Stems with yellow cork B. Branch with inflorescences. C. Flowers with some floral visitors. D. Frontal view of a flower. E. Frontal view of a flower, showing the gynostegium. F. Lateral view of a flower, showing the gynostegium. Photos by Victor W. Steinmann." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346250/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346254>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Maps showing the occurrence of Polystemma stevensii." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346254/files/figure.png" ;
